<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="abcb-glossentry" ?><abcb-glossentry xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_448dd81f-b4c5-4c29-9aec-d57b83b33db5" outputclass="abcb-glossentry"><glossterm id="_63a064f1-1a40-4483-bf14-afec51c74b24">Flight</glossterm><glossdef outputclass="glossdef"><p>That part of a stair that has a continuous series of <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1440_5.0.0.xml#_c719036a-be6e-4810-9535-cd37da0577cd" id="_916a494c-226c-4305-8634-c835e8659852" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">risers</xref>, including <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1440_5.0.0.xml#_c719036a-be6e-4810-9535-cd37da0577cd" id="_ef5ec1e7-edd9-4238-9b03-d317f912ac65" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">risers</xref> of <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1524_28.1.0.xml#_4a79e839-3915-459c-9c21-77379a801832" id="_a92e1930-d9fd-49a9-8d06-c44f191492d0" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">winders</xref>, not interrupted by a <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1357_2.1.0.xml#_68f79d99-aa42-455d-86ad-cae355bfc435" id="_4f0c1785-6f62-4371-acc6-5a242b97b836" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">landing</xref> or floor.</p><callout id="_bfc5bccb-9272-4ef3-8b45-badc302176c6"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>A <xref format="dita" href="#_63a064f1-1a40-4483-bf14-afec51c74b24" id="_654c5177-3b0e-4179-83b6-878f43c15a16" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="glossterm">flight</xref> is the part of a stair that has a continuous slope created by the nosing line of treads. The length of a <xref format="dita" href="#_63a064f1-1a40-4483-bf14-afec51c74b24" id="_79e7edfd-ca17-42d0-a8e0-56ec8dd3ba15" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="glossterm">flight</xref> is limited to restrict the distance a person could fall down a stair.</p><p>Quarter <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1357_2.1.0.xml#_68f79d99-aa42-455d-86ad-cae355bfc435" id="_e2b668b6-8e2f-427e-9448-5a353b9e8779" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">landings</xref>, as shown in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/2318_0.10.0.xml#_eb38b91c-3b60-49ad-b571-a1741f6c3f12" id="_690548c3-9987-4538-b83e-cd5466ffd935" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Explanatory Figure 1</xref>, are considered sufficient to halt a personâ€™s fall and therefore are considered for the purposes of NCC Volume Two and the ABCB Housing Provisions not to be part of the <xref format="dita" href="#_63a064f1-1a40-4483-bf14-afec51c74b24" id="_fc619812-d715-43dc-bf8d-184ea6e8ab03" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="glossterm">flight</xref>.</p><image-reference conref="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/2318_0.10.0.xml" id="_eb38b91c-3b60-49ad-b571-a1741f6c3f12"><num/><title id="_f130db15-b0ce-4c74-858b-c0a1c717685c"/></image-reference></callout></glossdef></abcb-glossentry>